00:16:56,732 --> 00:16:58,699
Over here!

280
00:16:58,734 --> 00:16:59,666
Clement?

281
00:16:59,702 --> 00:17:02,736
Serena, Bonnie,
this is incredible!

282
00:17:02,772 --> 00:17:06,573
This is the Azoth Kingdom!

283
00:17:06,609 --> 00:17:09,543
The Azoth Kingdom?

284
00:17:09,578 --> 00:17:11,578
It's an ultra-mechanized city.

285
00:17:11,614 --> 00:17:13,580
We'll find the great
scientist Nicola

286
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:15,582
using arcane science and art.

287
00:17:15,618 --> 00:17:16,583
[LAUGHING]

288
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:19,319
Mechanized?

289
00:17:19,355 --> 00:17:20,621
Nicola was a genius.

290
00:17:20,656 --> 00:17:23,690
He's truly one of
my all-time idols.

291
00:17:23,726 --> 00:17:26,593
He used Pokemon
skills as inspiration

292
00:17:26,629 --> 00:17:28,495
for his many inventions.

293
00:17:28,531 --> 00:17:31,298
Truly a great man.

294
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:31,765
[INAUDIBLE].

295
00:17:36,772 --> 00:17:39,706
[INAUDIBLE].

296
00:17:39,742 --> 00:17:42,676
[GRUNTING]

297
00:17:42,711 --> 00:17:44,344
[GASPING]

298
00:17:45,381 --> 00:17:47,781
Huh?

299
00:17:47,817 --> 00:17:48,782
[CHUCKLE]

300
00:17:48,818 --> 00:17:50,584
Pikaboo.

301
00:17:50,619 --> 00:17:51,552
[CHUCKLE]

302
00:17:53,789 --> 00:17:55,756
[STOMPING]

303
00:17:55,791 --> 00:17:56,757
[GRUNT]

304
00:18:00,563 --> 00:18:01,695
[ROBOT NOISES]

305
00:18:01,730 --> 00:18:05,599
For you, I would walk
through fire and water.

306
00:18:05,634 --> 00:18:07,301
Pika-pi!

307
00:18:07,336 --> 00:18:08,702
Pikachu!

308
00:18:08,737 --> 00:18:10,604
[ROBOT NOISES]

309
00:18:10,639 --> 00:18:13,307
So they call you
Volcanion, don't they?

310
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:16,276
Mm, and what do they do?

311
00:18:16,312 --> 00:18:16,743
[ROBOT NOISES]

312
00:18:19,682 --> 00:18:23,717
Magearna, you really are
a one-of-a-kind Pokemon.

313
00:18:23,752 --> 00:18:24,685
Pika.

314
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:26,687
Hahaha.

315
00:18:26,722 --> 00:18:28,355
Magearna, everything OK?

316
00:18:28,390 --> 00:18:29,523
[ROBOT NOISE]

317
00:18:29,558 --> 00:18:32,526
My name's Ash, And
this is my pal Pikachu.

318
00:18:32,561 --> 00:18:33,694
Pika, Pikachu.

319
00:18:33,729 --> 00:18:34,695
[ROBOT NOISE]

320
00:18:34,730 --> 00:18:35,762
[GRUNT]

321
00:18:35,798 --> 00:18:37,598
It's nice to meet you too.

322
00:18:37,633 --> 00:18:38,565
[GRUNT]

323
00:18:38,601 --> 00:18:41,368
Don't touch it!

324
00:18:41,403 --> 00:18:42,369
[BELL DINGS]

325
00:18:43,439 --> 00:18:44,371
Pika.

326
00:18:52,681 --> 00:18:54,581
Hey, what are you doing?

327
00:18:54,617 --> 00:18:56,650
I can't blast
anything without water.

328
00:18:56,685 --> 00:18:57,684
You can't?

329
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:58,652
Pika.

330
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:02,456
Don't worry.

331
00:19:02,491 --> 00:19:05,559
If those guys show up again,
we'll chase them away.

332
00:19:05,594 --> 00:19:08,662
I don't from humans.

333
00:19:08,697 --> 00:19:09,630
Pikachu.

334
00:19:09,665 --> 00:19:11,632
Stay out of this,
electric nuisance.

335
00:19:11,667 --> 00:19:12,699
Pika.

336
00:19:12,735 --> 00:19:13,634
Pika-eh-kachu!

337
00:19:16,572 --> 00:19:17,404
Listen up.

338
00:19:17,439 --> 00:19:19,373
I'll tell you just one.

339
00:19:19,408 --> 00:19:22,643
I will never trust humans.

340
00:19:22,678 --> 00:19:25,546
To Pokemon like you
that cozy up to humans,

341
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:27,681
I don't trust them either.

342
00:19:27,716 --> 00:19:29,583
Pika, Pika.

343
00:19:29,618 --> 00:19:30,651
What, Pipsqueak?

344
00:19:30,686 --> 00:19:33,654
What to fight?

345
00:19:33,689 --> 00:19:34,621
Come on.

346
00:19:34,657 --> 00:19:36,557
Everybody just calm down now.

347
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:37,558
[GRUMBLE]

348
00:19:37,593 --> 00:19:38,759
[ROBOT NOISES]

349
00:19:40,596 --> 00:19:41,562
Pik.

350
00:19:41,597 --> 00:19:43,397
Pika.

351
00:19:43,432 --> 00:19:44,698
We found them!

352
00:19:44,733 --> 00:19:47,634
[PANTING] Ash!

353
00:19:47,670 --> 00:19:49,603
everyone!

354
00:19:49,638 --> 00:19:50,604
Huh?

355
00:19:50,639 --> 00:19:53,774
[ROBOT NOISE]

356
00:19:53,809 --> 00:19:55,642
JARVIS: I see.

357
00:19:55,678 --> 00:19:59,313
You say that you know
that young boy trainer.

358
00:19:59,348 --> 00:20:00,714
Boy, do we ever.

359
00:20:00,749 --> 00:20:02,649
Quite-- for a very long time.

360
00:20:02,685 --> 00:20:03,617
Too long.

361
00:20:03,652 --> 00:20:04,685
You have no idea.

362
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:06,720
And you call
yourselves Team Rocket.

363
00:20:06,755 --> 00:20:07,788
I'll need more information.

364
00:20:07,823 --> 00:20:09,423
TOGETHER: More?

365
00:20:09,458 --> 00:20:10,390
Sure!

366
00:20:13,762 --> 00:20:16,396
Just meeting the
mythical Pokemon Volcanion

367
00:20:16,432 --> 00:20:17,631
would've been amazing.

368
00:20:17,666 --> 00:20:21,401
But to actually meet Nicola's
greatest creation of all time?

369
00:20:21,437 --> 00:20:22,703
I'm honored!

370
00:20:22,738 --> 00:20:23,704
[ROBOT NOISE]

371
00:20:23,739 --> 00:20:24,671
Mm.

372
00:20:24,707 --> 00:20:25,672
[CRACKLE]

373
00:20:25,708 --> 00:20:28,375
Huh?

374
00:20:28,410 --> 00:20:29,409
It's never coming off.

375
00:20:29,445 --> 00:20:30,377
Pika.

376
00:20:30,412 --> 00:20:32,746
You humans are useless.

377
00:20:32,781 --> 00:20:33,747
That's not nice.

378
00:20:33,782 --> 00:20:35,582
[INAUDIBLE].

379
00:20:35,618 --> 00:20:36,416
I'm sorry.

380
00:20:36,452 --> 00:20:37,618
Please forgive me.

381
00:20:37,653 --> 00:20:38,652
Huh?

382
00:20:38,687 --> 00:20:39,620
[GASP]

383
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:42,589
[ROBOT NOISES]

384
00:20:42,625 --> 00:20:45,392
[DELIGHTED GASP]

385
00:20:45,427 --> 00:20:46,760
Thank you, Magearna.

386
00:20:46,795 --> 00:20:48,629
You're a Pokemon treasure.

387
00:20:48,664 --> 00:20:49,830
Don't touch it!

388
00:20:49,865 --> 00:20:50,831
Huh?

389
00:20:50,866 --> 00:20:52,366
Look out!

390
00:20:52,401 --> 00:20:52,799
Wah!

391
00:20:52,835 --> 00:20:54,768
Pika!

392
00:20:54,803 --> 00:20:56,737
[GROANING]

393
00:20:58,874 --> 00:21:00,474
Why me?

394
00:21:00,509 --> 00:21:01,441
Ugh.

395
00:21:01,477 --> 00:21:02,442
(SADLY) Pika.

396
00:21:02,478 --> 00:21:03,410
Hi, there!

397
00:21:03,445 --> 00:21:04,444
We're back!

398
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:05,579
Huh?

399
00:21:05,614 --> 00:21:06,446
Magearna?

400
00:21:10,386 --> 00:21:11,618
[ROBOT NOISE]

401
00:21:11,654 --> 00:21:12,619
[AMAZED GASPS]

402
00:21:12,688 --> 00:21:13,620
Amazing!

403
00:21:13,656 --> 00:21:14,788
Incredible!

404
00:21:14,823 --> 00:21:15,789
[LAUGHING]

405
00:21:15,824 --> 00:21:17,457
Kind of like a Poke Ball.

406
00:21:17,493 --> 00:21:18,759
- Pikachu.
- Ash?

407
00:21:18,794 --> 00:21:19,760
Huh?

408
00:21:19,795 --> 00:21:20,894
Tada!

409
00:21:20,929 --> 00:21:24,698
Since your clothes are a
mess, how about you try these?

410
00:21:24,733 --> 00:21:27,334
Hmm.

411
00:21:27,369 --> 00:21:29,770
Uh-- hmm.

412
00:21:29,805 --> 00:21:31,705
Wow, you look great.

413
00:21:31,740 --> 00:21:32,639
Really?

414
00:21:32,675 --> 00:21:34,675
Pikachu, Magearna, do I?

415
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:36,343
Pika-Pika!

416
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:38,345
[EXCITED ROBOT NOISE]

417
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:40,614
Stop it, Magearna.

418
00:21:40,649 --> 00:21:42,482
Don't get involved
with these humans.

419
00:21:42,518 --> 00:21:45,752
[ROBOT NOISES]

420
00:21:45,788 --> 00:21:47,421
I refuse.

421
00:21:47,456 --> 00:21:48,488
[ROBOT NOISES]

422
00:21:48,524 --> 00:21:49,456
Leave me alone!

423
00:21:49,491 --> 00:21:51,358
[ROBOT NOISES]

424
00:21:53,395 --> 00:21:54,361
[POOF]

425
00:21:54,396 --> 00:21:55,629
[GASP]

426
00:21:59,668 --> 00:22:02,469
[GEARING UP TO SNEEZE]

427
00:22:03,472 --> 00:22:04,771
[ROARING]

428
00:22:04,807 --> 00:22:05,739
Choo!

429
00:22:10,446 --> 00:22:11,545
[GRUMBLE]

430
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:14,381
Hey, I told you to
quit it, didn't I?

431
00:22:17,119 --> 00:22:17,617
OK, fine.

432
00:22:17,653 --> 00:22:19,419
I'll doing my best.

433
00:22:19,488 --> 00:22:22,122
[ROBOT NOISES]

434
00:22:23,459 --> 00:22:24,424
[SPLASH]

435
00:22:24,460 --> 00:22:25,292
Aah!

436
00:22:25,327 --> 00:22:26,226
Magearna!

437
00:22:29,231 --> 00:22:31,164
[ALL GRUNTING]

438
00:22:35,237 --> 00:22:36,503
Are you all right?

439
00:22:36,538 --> 00:22:39,206
[ROBOT NOISES]

440
00:22:42,177 --> 00:22:43,410
Magearna, you're soaking wet.

441
00:22:43,445 --> 00:22:46,179
We'll get you all dried up.

442
00:22:46,215 --> 00:22:47,414
[ROBOT NOISES]

443
00:22:47,483 --> 00:22:49,216
Well, that's a relief.

444
00:22:49,251 --> 00:22:51,485
Though you've got to
admit, Magearna's heavy.

445
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:53,220
[ROBOT NOISES]

446
00:22:54,189 --> 00:22:55,155
Gearna?

447
00:22:55,190 --> 00:22:56,156
Pika?

448
00:22:56,191 --> 00:22:59,426
It looks embarrassed.

449
00:22:59,461 --> 00:23:00,560
Because it fell?

450
00:23:00,596 --> 00:23:04,131
I don't like Magearna
likes being called heavy.

451
00:23:04,166 --> 00:23:05,465
You're kidding.

452
00:23:05,501 --> 00:23:08,135
Of course it
doesn't like that.

453
00:23:08,170 --> 00:23:09,469
[GASP]

454
00:23:09,505 --> 00:23:11,204
I'm so very sorry.

455
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:12,205
Please forgive me.

456
00:23:12,241 --> 00:23:14,407
Clemont means
well, but he just

457
00:23:14,443 --> 00:23:16,209
doesn't understand some things.

458
00:23:16,245 --> 00:23:17,244
[GIGGLE]

459
00:23:17,279 --> 00:23:18,178
We should go.

460
00:23:18,213 --> 00:23:19,279
The sun is setting.

461
00:23:19,314 --> 00:23:21,481
[ROBOT NOISES]

462
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:27,254
No.

463
00:23:27,289 --> 00:23:30,524
I said, no!

464
00:23:30,559 --> 00:23:34,427
I won't bring humans along.

465
00:23:34,463 --> 00:23:36,396
Hey, where you going?

466
00:23:36,431 --> 00:23:39,399
Come back!

467
00:23:39,434 --> 00:23:40,400
Huh?

468
00:23:40,435 --> 00:23:43,103
Not again.

469
00:23:43,138 --> 00:23:44,571
[YELLING]

470
00:23:46,341 --> 00:23:47,274
Pika-pi!

471
00:23:49,611 --> 00:23:50,544
Huh?

472
00:23:50,579 --> 00:23:53,146
[MURMURING]

473
00:23:55,217 --> 00:23:58,585
We need to get away right now.

474
00:23:58,620 --> 00:24:01,121
[ROBOT NOISES]

475
00:24:01,156 --> 00:24:02,455
Get moving, or I'll
leave you behind.

476
00:24:13,335 --> 00:24:15,168
Raleigh, wait.

477
00:24:15,204 --> 00:24:16,136
Chymia!

478
00:24:16,171 --> 00:24:17,170
What is it?

479
00:24:17,206 --> 00:24:19,539
I saw you standing up
on the tower wall before.

480
00:24:19,575 --> 00:24:22,175
And you were with Alva, as well.

481
00:24:22,211 --> 00:24:23,176
What were you up to?

482
00:24:23,212 --> 00:24:25,312
A scientific investigation.

483
00:24:25,347 --> 00:24:27,314
Many of the amazing
machines built by Nicola

484
00:24:27,349 --> 00:24:29,282
are operating even now.

485
00:24:29,318 --> 00:24:30,517
Oh, is that all?

486
00:24:30,552 --> 00:24:32,085
Listen to me.

487
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:34,287
If you really want to
learn, look to the future,

488
00:24:34,323 --> 00:24:35,522
not just to the past.

489
00:24:35,557 --> 00:24:36,623
The future?

490
00:24:36,658 --> 00:24:39,125
To do that, you need to
learn about the past, see?

491
00:24:43,131 --> 00:24:45,332
Father is worried
about you, as well.

492
00:24:45,367 --> 00:24:48,235
Alva was with me, so
there was no need to worry.

493
00:24:48,270 --> 00:24:50,570
But that's why he's worried.

494
00:24:50,606 --> 00:24:52,339
Now, you know that
father trusts Alva

495
00:24:52,374 --> 00:24:54,474
completely, just like I do.

496
00:24:54,509 --> 00:25:00,146
He thinks a lot more about our
kingdom's future than you do.

497
00:25:00,182 --> 00:25:03,316
So if you'll please
excuse me, I have to go.

498
00:25:14,296 --> 00:25:16,062
1, 2--

499
00:25:16,098 --> 00:25:17,264
BOTH: Ta-da!

500
00:25:17,299 --> 00:25:18,231
Whoa!

501
00:25:18,267 --> 00:25:21,268
Isn't it cute, Volcanion?

502
00:25:21,303 --> 00:25:23,503
[BLOOPING]

503
00:25:26,508 --> 00:25:28,108
[SIGH]

504
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:33,513
Huh?

505
00:25:33,548 --> 00:25:35,482
Well, that went over well.

506
00:25:35,517 --> 00:25:37,117
Maybe it's shy.

507
00:25:37,152 --> 00:25:38,084
Could be.

508
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:39,152
Right, Magearna?

509
00:25:39,187 --> 00:25:41,221
[BEEPING]

510
00:25:41,256 --> 00:25:42,555
Getting friendly, aren't they?

511
00:25:42,591 --> 00:25:44,324
Sure are.

512
00:25:44,359 --> 00:25:47,494
Since we're stuck together
now, might as well have fun.

513
00:25:47,529 --> 00:25:49,296
- I agree.
- Nonsense.

514
00:25:49,331 --> 00:25:51,097
I just want to
get away from you.

515
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:53,199
Nothing good comes from
interacting with humans.

516
00:25:53,235 --> 00:25:54,134
Huh?

517
00:25:54,169 --> 00:25:55,502
You fell out of the
sky with these bands.

518
00:25:55,537 --> 00:25:56,369
Remember?

519
00:25:56,405 --> 00:25:58,571
Look, humans
made these things.

520
00:25:58,607 --> 00:26:00,340
Well, it sure wasn't us.

521
00:26:00,375 --> 00:26:02,208
All humans are the same.

522
00:26:02,244 --> 00:26:03,176
Pika!

523
00:26:07,282 --> 00:26:08,315
Hey, you.

524
00:26:08,350 --> 00:26:11,184
What are you doing
hanging around like that?

525
00:26:11,219 --> 00:26:14,187
Get your filthy
human hands off me.

526
00:26:14,222 --> 00:26:15,188
No, I won't!

527
00:26:15,223 --> 00:26:16,189
Cut it out, I said.

528
00:26:16,224 --> 00:26:17,490
No, you first!

529
00:26:17,526 --> 00:26:19,492
I'll blast you off.

530
00:26:28,570 --> 00:26:29,502
Agh.

531
00:26:33,342 --> 00:26:35,108
JARVIS: If they're
headed somewhere,

532
00:26:35,143 --> 00:26:37,510
it's probably Nebel Plateau.

533
00:26:37,546 --> 00:26:40,246
Oh, the place with the field
of flowers where Magearna was

534
00:26:40,282 --> 00:26:41,214
found.

535
00:26:41,249 --> 00:26:43,216
Yes.

536
00:26:43,251 --> 00:26:46,486
Members of Team Rocket,
please go investigate.

537
00:26:46,521 --> 00:26:48,288
Count on us, sir!

538
00:26:48,323 --> 00:26:50,290
[GIGGLING]

539
00:26:50,325 --> 00:26:52,158
It's all finished!

540
00:26:52,194 --> 00:26:53,093
What is?

541
00:26:53,128 --> 00:26:54,527
Have a look for yourselves.

542
00:26:54,563 --> 00:26:57,230
The future is now,
thanks to science.

543
00:27:02,170 --> 00:27:05,071
I made this protective
suits inspired by moves

544
00:27:05,107 --> 00:27:07,107
like iron defense and protect.

545
00:27:07,142 --> 00:27:08,341
It's called Mr. Iron Defense.

546
00:27:08,377 --> 00:27:09,309
Whoa-ho!

547
00:27:12,147 --> 00:27:14,247
You're protected from
any kind of attack.

548
00:27:16,385 --> 00:27:17,317
Huh?

549
00:27:17,352 --> 00:27:19,152
What do I see?

550
00:27:19,187 --> 00:27:21,054
It looks like a camp fire.

551
00:27:21,089 --> 00:27:23,223
Maybe they're setting
up camp here tonight.

552
00:27:23,258 --> 00:27:25,125
We have to tell Alva.

553
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:26,092
Wait.

554
00:27:26,128 --> 00:27:28,261
Our real boss is the prince.

555
00:27:28,296 --> 00:27:31,264
Once we can get our hands on
what he wants, we'll be rich.

556
00:27:31,299 --> 00:27:32,332
Brilliant!

557
00:27:32,367 --> 00:27:34,067
And that's rich.

558
00:27:34,102 --> 00:27:35,368
Let's make some dough.

559
00:27:35,404 --> 00:27:38,371
[SNORING]

560
00:27:42,577 --> 00:27:43,410
Huh?

561
00:27:43,445 --> 00:27:45,111
You sensed it, too?

562
00:27:53,388 --> 00:27:54,354
Pika.

563
00:27:54,389 --> 00:27:55,321
Pikachu!

564
00:27:58,193 --> 00:27:59,125
Ah!

565
00:27:59,161 --> 00:28:01,061
Huh?

566
00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:03,229
Uh, Magearna!

567
00:28:03,265 --> 00:28:05,231
[BEEPING]

568
00:28:05,267 --> 00:28:06,332
JAMES: Yoo-hoo!

569
00:28:06,368 --> 00:28:08,301
ALL: Huh?

570
00:28:08,336 --> 00:28:10,270
From now on,
Magearna's our guest.

571
00:28:10,305 --> 00:28:11,271
Team Rocket?

572
00:28:11,306 --> 00:28:13,073
What are you guys doing here?

573
00:28:13,108 --> 00:28:13,640
Huh?

574
00:28:13,675 --> 00:28:15,208
Heracross and Pinsir?

575
00:28:15,243 --> 00:28:17,310
Hey, where are
your normal Pokemon?

576
00:28:17,345 --> 00:28:20,046
We're not your
normal Team Rocket.

577
00:28:20,082 --> 00:28:20,947
Check this out.

578
00:28:20,982 --> 00:28:23,383
TEAM ROCKET: Mega
Wave Team Rocket!

579
00:28:23,418 --> 00:28:24,350
What?

580
00:28:24,419 --> 00:28:26,219
Key Stones!

581
00:28:26,254 --> 00:28:29,222
We joined forces with
the good Prince Raleigh.

582
00:28:29,257 --> 00:28:30,156
No way!

583
00:28:30,192 --> 00:28:31,124
See?

584
00:28:31,159 --> 00:28:32,358
We're Mega Wave Team Rocket!

585
00:28:35,363 --> 00:28:36,262
[GASP]

586
00:28:36,298 --> 00:28:37,263
Pika.

587
00:28:37,299 --> 00:28:38,231
Mega Wave!

588
00:28:48,176 --> 00:28:49,109
[SNARLING]

589
00:28:49,144 --> 00:28:50,276
Mega Evolve?

590
00:28:50,312 --> 00:28:51,244
But how?

591
00:28:51,279 --> 00:28:53,213
To Mega Evolve, there
must be a close bond

592
00:28:53,248 --> 00:28:55,181
between trainer and Pokemon.

593
00:28:55,217 --> 00:28:59,252
It's thanks to what Alva
calls-- er, what was it?

594
00:28:59,287 --> 00:29:00,220
Mm.

595
00:29:00,255 --> 00:29:02,355
Neo arcane science.

596
00:29:02,390 --> 00:29:05,091
With this technology, we
can use Mega Evolution

597
00:29:05,127 --> 00:29:07,093
and we don't need
any stinking bond!

598
00:29:07,129 --> 00:29:08,128
I see.

599
00:29:08,163 --> 00:29:09,395
So Gengar and the others--

600
00:29:09,431 --> 00:29:11,397
[SNARLING]

601
00:29:11,433 --> 00:29:13,166
Gengar!

602
00:29:13,201 --> 00:29:15,101
What about how
the Pokemon feel?

603
00:29:15,137 --> 00:29:17,070
That's not Mega Evolution!

604
00:29:17,105 --> 00:29:19,105
Arcane science was
developed to make

605
00:29:19,141 --> 00:29:20,306
people and Pokemon happy!

606
00:29:20,342 --> 00:29:23,243
You're defaming the
memory of Nicola!

607
00:29:23,278 --> 00:29:24,210
Hey!

608
00:29:24,246 --> 00:29:27,080
We call it neo because
technology passed

609
00:29:27,115 --> 00:29:28,348
through by science, guys.

610
00:29:28,383 --> 00:29:29,282
Now, Heracross!

611
00:29:29,317 --> 00:29:30,250
Pinsir, too!

612
00:29:30,285 --> 00:29:34,053
Turn them into goo!

613
00:29:34,089 --> 00:29:35,155
[SCREAMING]

614
00:29:35,190 --> 00:29:37,357
You, take Magearna
away from here.

615
00:29:37,392 --> 00:29:40,293
I hate relying on humans,
but I have no choice.

616
00:29:40,328 --> 00:29:42,061
Go!

617
00:29:42,097 --> 00:29:43,062
Everyone, do it.

618
00:29:43,098 --> 00:29:44,063
All right.

619
00:29:44,099 --> 00:29:44,497
Let's go, Magearna.

620
00:29:44,533 --> 00:29:47,267
Leave it to us.

621
00:29:47,302 --> 00:29:50,170
Let 'er rip.

622
00:29:50,205 --> 00:29:51,304
Pikachu, use Thunderbolt!

623
00:29:51,339 --> 00:29:52,272
Pikachu!

624
00:30:05,453 --> 00:30:06,386
Get him, Volcanion!

625
00:30:06,421 --> 00:30:08,288
I don't need a cheerleader.

626
00:30:19,534 --> 00:30:20,500
Yes!

627
00:30:20,535 --> 00:30:21,467
Pika.

628
00:30:30,378 --> 00:30:32,145
[SCREAMING]

629
00:30:33,515 --> 00:30:34,480
Success!

630
00:30:34,516 --> 00:30:37,183
It worked like a charm.

631
00:30:37,219 --> 00:30:40,186
Mega Evolution
drew Volcanion away.

632
00:30:40,222 --> 00:30:42,188
[SCREAMING]

633
00:30:42,457 --> 00:30:43,389
Gardevoir.

634
00:30:47,195 --> 00:30:48,161
The nerve!

635
00:30:59,341 --> 00:31:02,308
Gardevoir, Mega Evolve!

636
00:31:02,344 --> 00:31:03,276
Gard!

637
00:31:12,254 --> 00:31:13,286
Gardevoir.

638
00:31:13,321 --> 00:31:15,388
MEOWTH: Now there's a
Mega Gardevoir in my face.

639
00:31:15,423 --> 00:31:17,223
Use Dazzling Gleam!

640
00:31:17,259 --> 00:31:18,191
Gardevoir!

641
00:31:25,433 --> 00:31:28,201
TEAM ROCKET: We're
blasting off again!

642
00:31:28,236 --> 00:31:30,169
[SCREAMING]

643
00:31:37,412 --> 00:31:38,311
Wow!

644
00:31:38,346 --> 00:31:39,279
Nothing.

645
00:31:44,519 --> 00:31:45,485
Pikachu!

646
00:31:45,520 --> 00:31:46,486
PIKACHU: Pika.

647
00:31:46,521 --> 00:31:48,488
Let 'em have it, Volcanion.

648
00:31:48,523 --> 00:31:50,256
Don't blame me
for the results.

649
00:31:50,292 --> 00:31:51,257
Don't worry.

650
00:32:07,409 --> 00:32:08,441
Pika Pika!

651
00:32:08,476 --> 00:32:10,476
Science is so amazing.

652
00:32:10,512 --> 00:32:11,477
Pika?

653
00:32:11,513 --> 00:32:12,445
Huh?

654
00:32:22,257 --> 00:32:24,157
So this is your real power.

655
00:32:24,192 --> 00:32:25,391
Ha.

656
00:32:25,427 --> 00:32:28,194
If I showed you my real power,
it wouldn't be just this.

657
00:32:28,229 --> 00:32:29,529
I've leveled a whole mountain.

658
00:32:29,564 --> 00:32:31,331
Awesome.

659
00:32:31,366 --> 00:32:32,298
Pika?

660
00:32:36,304 --> 00:32:37,470
Hey, Ash!

661
00:32:37,505 --> 00:32:39,505
What exploded?

662
00:32:39,541 --> 00:32:41,474
Hey, guys.

663
00:32:41,509 --> 00:32:42,442
Pika!

664
00:32:42,477 --> 00:32:44,344
Now I've got even more humans.

665
00:32:50,218 --> 00:32:53,519
Magearna, I'm Chymia,
princess of Azoth.

666
00:32:53,555 --> 00:32:56,255
Pleased to meet you.

667
00:32:56,291 --> 00:32:58,491
I'm a descendant of
the Azoth royal family.

668
00:32:58,526 --> 00:32:59,459
Princess?

669
00:32:59,494 --> 00:33:00,393
Whoa.

670
00:33:00,428 --> 00:33:01,427
[BEEPING]

671
00:33:20,281 --> 00:33:22,315
[BEEPING]

672
00:33:22,350 --> 00:33:23,316
[GASP]

673
00:33:23,351 --> 00:33:24,250
Oh, my.

674
00:33:24,285 --> 00:33:25,385
They're beautiful.

675
00:33:25,420 --> 00:33:26,519
Thank you.

676
00:33:26,554 --> 00:33:30,456
Volcanion, you were
protecting Magearna, right?

677
00:33:33,261 --> 00:33:34,193
Hm.

678
00:33:37,949 --> 00:33:39,215
CHYMIA: For the kingdom?

679
00:33:39,250 --> 00:33:41,117
That's what Raleigh said, huh?

680
00:33:41,152 --> 00:33:42,118
SERENA: Right.

681
00:33:42,153 --> 00:33:43,386
One thing's for sure.

682
00:33:43,421 --> 00:33:47,223
Raleigh believes everything that
Alva tells him-- that it's all

683
00:33:47,258 --> 00:33:49,092
for the good of the kingdom.

684
00:33:49,127 --> 00:33:52,128
Does Raleigh really trust
this Alva person that much?

685
00:33:52,163 --> 00:33:53,096
Yes.

686
00:33:56,201 --> 00:34:00,103
Ever since Raleigh was a
boy, he always adored Nicola.

687
00:34:00,138 --> 00:34:03,039
Many times, he would spend
the entire day in his room,

688
00:34:03,074 --> 00:34:07,810
reading old texts and
performing experiments.

689
00:34:07,846 --> 00:34:10,279
And because of that, when he
found out that Councilor Alva

690
00:34:10,315 --> 00:34:13,082
was an arcane
science researcher,

691
00:34:13,118 --> 00:34:16,018
he started to spend more
and more time with him.

692
00:34:20,291 --> 00:34:23,826
So now, since my brother
is involved in this,

693
00:34:23,862 --> 00:34:25,161
that means that I am, too.

694
00:34:28,066 --> 00:34:29,198
[YELLING]

695
00:34:32,003 --> 00:34:33,236
Hey, why don't we
just get on board

696
00:34:33,271 --> 00:34:35,037
the thing they're riding on?

697
00:34:35,073 --> 00:34:37,173
Why would I board
something humans built?

698
00:34:37,208 --> 00:34:40,309
Oh, come on.

699
00:34:40,345 --> 00:34:41,277
Ah!

700
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:50,253
[GASP]

701
00:34:50,288 --> 00:34:52,188
The princess.

702
00:34:52,223 --> 00:34:54,323
I know.

703
00:34:54,359 --> 00:34:55,324
Dedenne.

704
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:56,292
Wow!

705
00:34:56,327 --> 00:34:57,260
A field of flowers!

706
00:35:02,267 --> 00:35:05,001
Come to greet us, huh?

707
00:35:05,036 --> 00:35:07,003
[FRANTIC CHIRPING]

708
00:35:07,038 --> 00:35:08,004
What?

709
00:35:08,039 --> 00:35:09,972
[CHIRP]

710
00:35:10,008 --> 00:35:11,174
Ah?

711
00:35:11,209 --> 00:35:12,175
Ah!

712
00:35:12,210 --> 00:35:13,976
Huh?

713
00:35:14,012 --> 00:35:16,846
[CHIRPING]

714
00:35:16,881 --> 00:35:17,847
Up ahead.

715
00:35:17,882 --> 00:35:19,081
Is that Amaura?

716
00:35:24,289 --> 00:35:27,089
Amaura's badly injured.

717
00:35:27,125 --> 00:35:29,225
Hold on.

718
00:35:29,260 --> 00:35:30,226
[WHIMPERING]

719
00:35:32,263 --> 00:35:33,196
Hang in there.

720
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:38,301
We'll take care of it.

721
00:35:38,336 --> 00:35:40,002
I don't need your help.

722
00:35:40,038 --> 00:35:41,103
I'll carry Amaura myself.

723
00:35:47,011 --> 00:35:48,144
[GROANING]

724
00:35:49,180 --> 00:35:50,112
[GRUNTING]

725
00:35:54,085 --> 00:35:56,319
Now this big one
will fetch me an even

726
00:35:56,354 --> 00:35:58,221
better price than that Amaura.

727
00:35:58,256 --> 00:36:01,991
A Pokemon hunter.

728
00:36:02,026 --> 00:36:04,160
[POWERING DOWN]

729
00:36:04,195 --> 00:36:05,161
[GASP]

730
00:36:05,196 --> 00:36:07,196
All right,
Pikachu, Thunderbolt!

731
00:36:07,232 --> 00:36:08,130
Pikachu!

732
00:36:11,870 --> 00:36:14,837
I'll fix all of you.

733
00:36:14,873 --> 00:36:16,138
[GROWLING]

734
00:36:38,997 --> 00:36:41,197
[CHIRPING]

735
00:36:41,232 --> 00:36:42,999
What a bad man.

736
00:36:43,034 --> 00:36:45,301
Pokemon hunters
only want one thing--

737
00:36:45,370 --> 00:36:48,037
to make money stealing Pokemon.

738
00:36:48,072 --> 00:36:51,007
So bad things like this--
do they happen a lot?

739
00:36:51,042 --> 00:36:52,108
Yes.

740
00:36:52,143 --> 00:36:55,011
But I can usually drive
them off by creating mist

741
00:36:55,046 --> 00:36:56,846
long before they get this far.

742
00:37:07,292 --> 00:37:08,257
[GASP]

743
00:37:08,293 --> 00:37:09,225
Pika.

744
00:37:14,065 --> 00:37:17,033
VOLCANION: This is
Nebel Plateau, our home.

745
00:37:24,108 --> 00:37:25,274
So many Pokemon!

746
00:37:25,310 --> 00:37:27,209
And they're totally cute!

747
00:37:37,889 --> 00:37:39,155
[BEEPING]

748
00:37:39,891 --> 00:37:41,123
- Drill.
- Pika, pika.

749
00:37:41,159 --> 00:37:42,091
Pika!

750
00:37:42,126 --> 00:37:44,093
Dedenne.

751
00:37:44,128 --> 00:37:45,061
Pika?

752
00:37:45,096 --> 00:37:46,262
Dedenne.

753
00:37:46,297 --> 00:37:48,898
Everybody seems
pretty afraid of us.

754
00:37:48,933 --> 00:37:50,132
You know why.

755
00:37:50,168 --> 00:37:51,934
You're humans, right?

756
00:37:51,970 --> 00:37:54,837
It does look like they
don't trust us at all.

757
00:37:54,872 --> 00:37:56,038
I wonder why that is.

758
00:38:01,212 --> 00:38:02,144
All right.

759
00:38:02,180 --> 00:38:03,879
I'll treat Amaura.
Don't worry.

760
00:38:03,915 --> 00:38:04,847
Treat.

761
00:38:04,882 --> 00:38:07,216
Don't just do whatever you want.

762
00:38:07,251 --> 00:38:08,184
Don't be so angry.

763
00:38:08,219 --> 00:38:11,120
You've got to trust
us a little bit.

764
00:38:11,155 --> 00:38:12,088
[BEEPING]

765
00:38:12,123 --> 00:38:13,856
You help, too, Bonnie.
BONNIE: Sure!

766
00:38:13,891 --> 00:38:14,890
CHYMIA: Let me help, too.

767
00:38:14,926 --> 00:38:15,925
I could help, too.

768
00:38:21,265 --> 00:38:22,832
Does it sting?

769
00:38:22,867 --> 00:38:23,899
It'll all be over soon.

770
00:38:23,935 --> 00:38:25,801
You've just got to be strong.

771
00:38:25,837 --> 00:38:26,268
Pika.

772
00:38:31,976 --> 00:38:34,076
CHYMIA: The bandage is freezing.

773
00:38:34,112 --> 00:38:37,046
This sort of thing happens
with ice type Pokemon.

774
00:38:37,081 --> 00:38:38,848
It's proof of the healing.

775
00:38:38,883 --> 00:38:40,182
That means the
medicine's working.

776
00:38:40,218 --> 00:38:42,284
Amaura, that's so great.

777
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:43,285
Dedenne-ne.

778
00:38:43,321 --> 00:38:45,187
Amaura.

779
00:38:45,223 --> 00:38:47,256
Forget all the bad times.

780
00:38:47,291 --> 00:38:49,291
You're in a safe place now.

781
00:38:49,327 --> 00:38:50,860
You have food here.

782
00:38:50,895 --> 00:38:52,294
You have friends, too.

783
00:38:52,330 --> 00:38:54,230
'Maura.

784
00:38:54,265 --> 00:38:55,831
Sleep now, Amaura.

785
00:38:59,871 --> 00:39:01,070
[BEEPING]

786
00:39:04,208 --> 00:39:07,843
[LULLABY MUSIC PLAYING]

787
00:39:16,220 --> 00:39:17,153
Pika!

788
00:39:49,220 --> 00:39:50,186
Pi?

789
00:39:50,221 --> 00:39:51,153
Huh?

790
00:39:54,192 --> 00:39:57,126
Pika?

791
00:39:57,161 --> 00:39:58,828
Pika.

792
00:39:58,863 --> 00:40:01,263
It must be that they're
scared because we're here.

793
00:40:01,299 --> 00:40:05,234
Well, we may be humans, but
Pokemon are still Pokemon.

794
00:40:05,269 --> 00:40:06,235
All right.

795
00:40:06,270 --> 00:40:08,237
Now, everybody out!

796
00:40:12,944 --> 00:40:14,977
Pancha-cha.

797
00:40:15,012 --> 00:40:16,245
Yeah!
Great idea.

798
00:40:16,280 --> 00:40:17,213
I'm in.

799
00:40:20,184 --> 00:40:21,016
Hawlucha.

800
00:40:21,052 --> 00:40:22,251
Talonflame.

801
00:40:22,286 --> 00:40:24,854
Bla, bluh.

802
00:40:24,889 --> 00:40:25,855
Bun!
Bunnelby!

803
00:40:25,890 --> 00:40:26,322
Luxray.

804
00:40:26,357 --> 00:40:27,289
You see?

805
00:40:27,325 --> 00:40:29,859
You don't need to
be afraid of us.

806
00:40:29,894 --> 00:40:33,262
Help us show them
we're friendly.

807
00:40:33,297 --> 00:40:34,230
Pikachu!

808
00:40:40,271 --> 00:40:42,204
Ch-ch-ch cha-cha-chu.

809
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:43,239
Che.

810
00:40:43,274 --> 00:40:44,173
Eee!

811
00:40:47,278 --> 00:40:48,177
Chu!

812
00:40:54,318 --> 00:40:55,985
Hawlucha.

813
00:40:56,020 --> 00:40:57,920
Cha-cha.

814
00:40:57,955 --> 00:40:58,921
Lucha.

815
00:40:58,956 --> 00:40:59,889
Lucha!

816
00:40:59,924 --> 00:41:00,356
Pikachu.

817
00:41:24,348 --> 00:41:26,015
[BEEPING]

818
00:41:26,050 --> 00:41:27,016
Wow, this is great!

819
00:41:27,051 --> 00:41:27,983
Yeah!

820
00:41:30,354 --> 00:41:31,287
Argh.

821
00:41:31,322 --> 00:41:33,222
Huh?

822
00:41:33,257 --> 00:41:34,924
Volcanion, are you OK?

823
00:41:34,959 --> 00:41:38,027
Hey, wait a minute--
the Pokemon hunter.

824
00:41:38,062 --> 00:41:39,295
You need help, too.

825
00:41:39,330 --> 00:41:40,930
I need nothing.

826
00:41:40,965 --> 00:41:44,166
Magearna, stay out of the
flower field for a while, OK?

827
00:41:46,971 --> 00:41:48,170
But what about you?

828
00:41:51,209 --> 00:41:52,041
Hey!

829
00:41:52,076 --> 00:41:53,008
Wait for me!

830
00:41:53,044 --> 00:41:53,976
Bonnie.

831
00:42:06,023 --> 00:42:08,224
ASH: It's a hot spring.

832
00:42:08,259 --> 00:42:09,992
BONNIE: Like a giant bath.

833
00:42:10,027 --> 00:42:12,995
A bath will fix me right up.

834
00:42:13,030 --> 00:42:13,963
Wow.

835
00:42:23,241 --> 00:42:27,009
Quick, Ash, you've got to
get out of there right away.

836
00:42:27,044 --> 00:42:28,877
Wha?

837
00:42:28,913 --> 00:42:29,878
Whoa!

838
00:42:29,914 --> 00:42:33,182
Your suit's
absorbing the water.

839
00:42:33,217 --> 00:42:34,883
[YELLING]

840
00:42:41,926 --> 00:42:43,192
Eugh, and then some.

841
00:42:47,231 --> 00:42:48,163
Hm.

842
00:42:48,199 --> 00:42:50,299
You humans are an
annoying bunch.

843
00:42:59,977 --> 00:43:00,876
Wrench, please.

844
00:43:00,911 --> 00:43:02,278
Bunnelby.

845
00:43:02,313 --> 00:43:04,013
Che.

846
00:43:04,048 --> 00:43:04,980
Thanks a lot.

847
00:43:10,221 --> 00:43:12,921
Working on gadgets
along with Pokemon.

848
00:43:12,957 --> 00:43:16,258
I'm sure it must have been
like this for Nicola, too.

849
00:43:16,294 --> 00:43:19,228
Nicola thought the world
needed both humans and Pokemon

850
00:43:19,263 --> 00:43:22,298
to be in harmony, which I
believe is what inspired

851
00:43:22,333 --> 00:43:24,833
him to create Magearna.

852
00:43:24,869 --> 00:43:27,236
Magearna's the living
embodiment of the philosophy

853
00:43:27,271 --> 00:43:29,972
of arcane science.

854
00:43:30,007 --> 00:43:33,242
At least, that's the way I
prefer to interpret that.

855
00:43:33,277 --> 00:43:35,010
It's such a beautiful idea.

856
00:43:39,250 --> 00:43:42,084
ASH: So you're always here,
watching out for everyone.

857
00:43:42,119 --> 00:43:43,152
Ha.

858
00:43:43,187 --> 00:43:46,221
That's because I never
know when I might explode.

859
00:43:46,257 --> 00:43:47,856
You've got that right.

860
00:43:47,892 --> 00:43:48,657
Pikachu.

861
00:43:48,693 --> 00:43:51,060
Why don't you
two get some sleep.

862
00:43:51,095 --> 00:43:53,295
You're keeping
watch, I am, too.

863
00:43:53,331 --> 00:43:55,264
Pika, Pikachu.

864
00:43:55,333 --> 00:43:56,999
Do as you like.

865
00:43:57,034 --> 00:43:58,067
I will.

866
00:43:58,102 --> 00:43:59,001
Pika-Pika.

867
00:44:08,279 --> 00:44:10,212
[CHUCKLING]

868
00:44:15,853 --> 00:44:17,820
Ta-da!

869
00:44:17,855 --> 00:44:20,789
Your clothes--
they're all clean.

870
00:44:20,825 --> 00:44:21,757
Wow.

871
00:44:21,792 --> 00:44:22,825
Thanks a lot, Serena.

872
00:44:22,860 --> 00:44:23,792
Pikachu!

873
00:44:34,805 --> 00:44:37,573
[BEEPING]

874
00:44:55,726 --> 00:44:57,025
Oh, boy.

875
00:44:57,061 --> 00:44:58,060
This won't be easy.

876
00:45:03,734 --> 00:45:04,666
Gulpin.

877
00:45:04,702 --> 00:45:05,634
Bunnelby.

878
00:45:11,575 --> 00:45:12,007
Yes!

879
00:45:17,014 --> 00:45:17,846
It worked!

880
00:45:32,830 --> 00:45:33,729
BONNIE: Yay!

881
00:45:33,764 --> 00:45:35,697
They brought those
berries for us.

882
00:45:42,039 --> 00:45:42,838
Hm.

883
00:45:42,873 --> 00:45:43,839
Incredible.

884
00:45:43,874 --> 00:45:46,608
I never thought I'd
see humans and Pokemon

885
00:45:46,644 --> 00:45:49,978
getting along together here.

886
00:45:50,014 --> 00:45:53,615
All these Pokemon--
they've been hurt by humans,

887
00:45:53,651 --> 00:45:54,049
haven't they?

888
00:45:54,084 --> 00:45:56,018
Yes, they have.

889
00:45:56,053 --> 00:45:58,787
You, too?

890
00:45:58,823 --> 00:46:00,656
Don't worry about
what happened to me.

891
00:46:07,631 --> 00:46:08,564
All fixed!

892
00:46:08,599 --> 00:46:09,565
Good as new.

893
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:11,967
Next time, we're going
to be working on you.

894
00:46:12,002 --> 00:46:12,968
Working on us?

895
00:46:13,003 --> 00:46:13,836
Pika?

896
00:46:17,575 --> 00:46:18,774
Watch what this one can do.

897
00:46:31,589 --> 00:46:32,721
It's about time.

898
00:46:32,756 --> 00:46:34,756
It worked!

899
00:46:34,792 --> 00:46:35,791
Thanks so much, Gulpin.

900
00:46:42,700 --> 00:46:43,599
Huh?

901
00:46:43,634 --> 00:46:44,600
Pika?

902
00:46:44,635 --> 00:46:46,835
This Gulpin has its reasons.

903
00:46:46,871 --> 00:46:48,804
Anyway, the bands are gone.

904
00:46:48,839 --> 00:46:50,806
Leave.

905
00:46:50,841 --> 00:46:53,041
Even after all
that's happened?

906
00:46:53,077 --> 00:46:55,844
After everybody's starting
to get along so well?

907
00:46:55,880 --> 00:46:57,579
Doesn't mean anything.

908
00:46:57,615 --> 00:46:58,680
It does, too.

909
00:46:58,716 --> 00:47:00,716
You only did that because
we were stuck together.

910
00:47:00,751 --> 00:47:02,851
Hey, I really like Pokemon.

911
00:47:02,887 --> 00:47:04,786
I want to protect them, too.

912
00:47:04,822 --> 00:47:06,722
If you're going to
be a Pokemon trainer,

913
00:47:06,757 --> 00:47:09,758
then you've got to learn how
to make Pokemon feel safe.

914
00:47:09,793 --> 00:47:12,995
Right, buddy?
- Pika, pika!

915
00:47:13,030 --> 00:47:16,565
Spare me your pretty
words or I'll blast you.

916
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:17,699
You try it!

917
00:47:17,735 --> 00:47:19,701
Pika!

918
00:47:19,737 --> 00:47:20,669
Bunnelby.

919
00:47:31,849 --> 00:47:33,582
I'm going to sleep.

920
00:47:33,617 --> 00:47:34,550
Aw.

921
00:48:11,956 --> 00:48:12,888
What?

922
00:48:12,923 --> 00:48:14,823
I brought Poke Puffs.

923
00:48:14,858 --> 00:48:16,792
Serena and Chymia made them.

924
00:48:16,827 --> 00:48:17,726
Pika.

925
00:48:17,761 --> 00:48:19,928
Huh?

926
00:48:19,964 --> 00:48:22,631
You were surprised
back there, weren't you?

927
00:48:22,666 --> 00:48:23,932
They just didn't understand.

928
00:48:23,968 --> 00:48:27,769
Please forgive them.

929
00:48:27,805 --> 00:48:28,770
Sorry, Gulpin.

930
00:48:28,806 --> 00:48:29,738
Pikachu.

931
00:48:35,613 --> 00:48:36,878
This little one
came here after being

932
00:48:36,914 --> 00:48:40,549
abandoned by its trainer.

933
00:48:40,584 --> 00:48:41,717
Pika.

934
00:48:41,752 --> 00:48:44,853
I don't know if anything
happened before that.

935
00:48:44,888 --> 00:48:47,923
He doesn't tell me,
and I don't ask.

936
00:48:47,958 --> 00:48:51,893
The only thing I know is that,
right before its trainer left,

937
00:48:51,929 --> 00:48:54,630
he gave Gulpin a big hug.

938
00:49:00,704 --> 00:49:04,673
All of the Pokemon here have
been wounded by the selfishness

939
00:49:04,708 --> 00:49:06,675
and lies of humans.

940
00:49:06,710 --> 00:49:12,881
They may be laughing now, but
their wounds are deeply-rooted.

941
00:49:12,916 --> 00:49:17,619
And that's the reason
I can't trust humans.

942
00:49:17,655 --> 00:49:21,823
Pokemon are incapable of
lying, but humans are.

943
00:49:21,859 --> 00:49:23,892
And do.

944
00:49:23,927 --> 00:49:24,860
Pika pika.

945
00:49:24,895 --> 00:49:25,827
Pika.

946
00:49:25,863 --> 00:49:26,795
Pika pi.

947
00:49:26,830 --> 00:49:27,763
Really?

948
00:49:27,798 --> 00:49:29,631
This one doesn't lie?

949
00:49:29,667 --> 00:49:30,599
Pika!

950
00:49:30,634 --> 00:49:31,667
Pikachu!

951
00:49:31,702 --> 00:49:32,868
Pikachu.

952
00:49:32,903 --> 00:49:37,673
He fights with all he has
to protect the ones he loves.

953
00:49:37,708 --> 00:49:38,674
Pika pika.

954
00:49:38,709 --> 00:49:39,841
Thank you for that.

955
00:49:39,877 --> 00:49:40,809
You're right.

956
00:49:40,844 --> 00:49:42,044
Pikachu!

957
00:49:42,079 --> 00:49:45,947
Both of you are spewing
nothing but flowery sentiments.

958
00:49:45,983 --> 00:49:47,883
I'm sorry.

959
00:49:47,918 --> 00:49:51,653
Before the others get used
to you, I want you to leave,

960
00:49:51,689 --> 00:49:53,789
though I'm very grateful
to you for what you

961
00:49:53,824 --> 00:49:55,757
did for Magearna and Amaura.

962
00:50:00,698 --> 00:50:01,897
Here.
Go ahead and eat.

963
00:50:11,809 --> 00:50:13,742
Not bad.

964
00:50:13,777 --> 00:50:16,678
If you like it, then why
don't you say you like it?

965
00:50:16,714 --> 00:50:17,646
Pikachu.

966
00:50:17,681 --> 00:50:18,046
Eat.

967
00:50:18,082 --> 00:50:19,014
Both of you.

968
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:25,854
[RUSTLING]
- Pi?

969
00:50:25,889 --> 00:50:26,788
Pika?

970
00:50:32,696 --> 00:50:34,730
What is that?

971
00:50:34,765 --> 00:50:35,897
[GROWLING]

972
00:50:35,966 --> 00:50:38,633
[ALL SQUEAKING]

973
00:50:43,974 --> 00:50:45,841
[GRUNTING]

974
00:50:49,847 --> 00:50:52,013
[GRUNTING]

975
00:50:52,049 --> 00:50:54,716
[ALL PANTING]

976
00:51:00,057 --> 00:51:02,758
[ALL SCREAMING]

977
00:51:07,765 --> 00:51:08,730
[ALL GASPING]

978
00:51:08,766 --> 00:51:10,665
[GROANING]

979
00:51:11,802 --> 00:51:13,769
Grexit, Talonflame!

980
00:51:13,804 --> 00:51:14,970
Luxray, Greninja!

981
00:51:15,005 --> 00:51:17,939
Woo!

982
00:51:17,975 --> 00:51:20,709
[ALL SHOUTING]

983
00:51:21,712 --> 00:51:24,846
[HOWLING]

984
00:51:24,882 --> 00:51:26,014
Everyone!

985
00:51:26,049 --> 00:51:27,816
[GASPS]

986
00:51:27,851 --> 00:51:29,885
Kanu!

987
00:51:29,920 --> 00:51:31,720
Dreberon.

988
00:51:31,755 --> 00:51:33,688
Jiyoo!

989
00:51:33,724 --> 00:51:34,856
[ALL SCREAMING]

990
00:51:34,892 --> 00:51:39,828
[GRUNTING]

991
00:51:39,863 --> 00:51:40,829
Huh?

992
00:51:40,864 --> 00:51:41,797
Huh?

993
00:51:41,832 --> 00:51:43,965
[ALL EXCLAIMING]

994
00:51:46,937 --> 00:51:47,836
You two.

995
00:51:50,808 --> 00:51:52,674
Well, well.

996
00:51:52,709 --> 00:51:53,675
[CLICK]

997
00:51:53,710 --> 00:51:55,811
[ALL MOANING]

998
00:51:59,016 --> 00:51:59,981
If you resist--

999
00:52:00,017 --> 00:52:00,882
[CLICK]

1000
00:52:00,918 --> 00:52:02,851
[ALL MOANING]

1001
00:52:07,024 --> 00:52:07,989
You're the worst.

1002
00:52:08,025 --> 00:52:08,924
Bega!

1003
00:52:08,959 --> 00:52:10,792
They're humans.

1004
00:52:10,828 --> 00:52:13,862
They think nothing of
the lives of Pokemon.

1005
00:52:13,897 --> 00:52:14,963
Hey!

1006
00:52:14,998 --> 00:52:16,698
I'll blast you!

1007
00:52:16,733 --> 00:52:17,899
Manectric, electrotrain!

1008
00:52:17,935 --> 00:52:20,802
Steelix, use stealth rocket.

1009
00:52:20,871 --> 00:52:23,672
Mey, nethra.

1010
00:52:23,707 --> 00:52:25,674
[SCREAMING]

1011
00:52:25,709 --> 00:52:26,842
[GASPING]

1012
00:52:26,877 --> 00:52:29,845
[GROWLING]

1013
00:52:29,880 --> 00:52:31,847
How dare you?

1014
00:52:35,819 --> 00:52:36,985
[SQUEAKING]

1015
00:52:37,020 --> 00:52:41,723
If you want to help them,
then you should come with us.

1016
00:52:41,758 --> 00:52:44,993
If you do, then
everybody is happy.

1017
00:52:45,028 --> 00:52:46,761
No!

1018
00:52:46,797 --> 00:52:47,796
Don't go, Magearna.

1019
00:52:47,831 --> 00:52:48,897
[GROWLING]

1020
00:52:48,932 --> 00:52:50,699
Then I've no choice.

1021
00:52:50,734 --> 00:52:51,666
[CLICK]

1022
00:52:51,702 --> 00:52:54,703
[ALL SCREAMING]

1023
00:52:54,738 --> 00:52:56,905
Oh, you'll pay for this!

1024
00:52:56,940 --> 00:52:59,708
Oh!

1025
00:52:59,743 --> 00:53:01,843
[BEEPING]

1026
00:53:05,048 --> 00:53:07,849
[GASPS] Magearna!

1027
00:53:07,885 --> 00:53:08,817
Heeda.

1028
00:53:12,990 --> 00:53:14,823
So now you understand.

1029
00:53:14,858 --> 00:53:15,991
[LAUGHS]

1030
00:53:16,026 --> 00:53:17,893
Use psychic.

1031
00:53:17,928 --> 00:53:18,994
Zob.

1032
00:53:19,029 --> 00:53:20,028
Oog nay.

1033
00:53:24,902 --> 00:53:25,867
Googi.

1034
00:53:25,903 --> 00:53:27,769
Magearna!

1035
00:53:27,804 --> 00:53:28,737
Ah.

1036
00:53:35,045 --> 00:53:36,778
[ALL GASPING]

1037
00:53:36,813 --> 00:53:37,979
[PANTING]

1038
00:53:42,819 --> 00:53:45,787
[GROWLING]

1039
00:53:45,822 --> 00:53:47,722
[BEEPING]

1040
00:53:48,091 --> 00:53:50,959
Rollie, Alva.

1041
00:53:50,994 --> 00:53:52,794
Everything's OK.

1042
00:53:52,829 --> 00:53:54,029
All of this is for our kingdom.

1043
00:53:54,064 --> 00:53:55,830
[CHUCKLES]

1044
00:53:55,866 --> 00:53:56,998
[SCOFFS]

1045
00:53:57,034 --> 00:53:59,968
[ROARS]

1046
00:54:00,003 --> 00:54:01,002
Oh.

1047
00:54:01,038 --> 00:54:03,838
Alva, why don't we
tell them everything,

1048
00:54:03,907 --> 00:54:06,841
What an incredible creation
Magearna really is?

1049
00:54:06,877 --> 00:54:07,776
Fine.

1050
00:54:07,811 --> 00:54:08,910
Gengar, mean look.

1051
00:54:08,946 --> 00:54:10,879
Gah.

1052
00:54:10,914 --> 00:54:11,880
[BEEPING]

1053
00:54:11,915 --> 00:54:12,847
Huh?

1054
00:54:12,883 --> 00:54:13,848
Ah.

1055
00:54:13,884 --> 00:54:16,017
[BEEPING]

1056
00:54:16,853 --> 00:54:17,786
Gah.

1057
00:54:20,924 --> 00:54:22,958
- [EVIL LAUGH]
- Wait a minute.

1058
00:54:22,993 --> 00:54:25,760
You don't have to
remove its soul-heart.

1059
00:54:25,796 --> 00:54:28,763
That's just as long as
Magearna becomes a spear.

1060
00:54:28,799 --> 00:54:30,799
Nicholas said that-- ah!

1061
00:54:30,834 --> 00:54:33,568
All that I really
need is its soul-heart.

1062
00:54:33,603 --> 00:54:34,135
You can't!

1063
00:54:34,171 --> 00:54:36,037
If you remove it, then--

1064
00:54:41,845 --> 00:54:44,012
[CHUCKLES]

1065
00:54:48,018 --> 00:54:50,018
Alva, what happened?

1066
00:54:50,053 --> 00:54:50,986
It's gone.

1067
00:54:51,021 --> 00:54:52,053
[GASPS]

1068
00:54:52,089 --> 00:54:54,923
Gengar, kindly
return Magearna.

1069
00:54:54,958 --> 00:54:56,992
[SNARLS]

1070
00:55:00,764 --> 00:55:01,696
[GASPS]

1071
00:55:01,732 --> 00:55:03,832
[SHOUTING]

1072
00:55:03,867 --> 00:55:08,570
Chymia, your presence is
not required for my plan.

1073
00:55:08,605 --> 00:55:09,838
Farewell.

1074
00:55:09,873 --> 00:55:11,539
Use hyperbeam.

1075
00:55:11,575 --> 00:55:13,541
[SHOUTING]

1076
00:55:19,883 --> 00:55:21,783
How could you lie to me?

1077
00:55:21,818 --> 00:55:23,752
It wasn't for the kingdom!

1078
00:55:23,787 --> 00:55:27,956
Yes, it was all done for the
glory of the Kingdom of Azoth,

1079
00:55:27,991 --> 00:55:30,592
my ideal one, of course.

1080
00:55:30,627 --> 00:55:31,960
[GASPS]

1081
00:55:31,995 --> 00:55:33,828
Gengar, hypnosis.

1082
00:55:33,864 --> 00:55:36,698
[SNARLING]

1083
00:56:00,741 --> 00:56:03,575
They used dig and safeguard.

1084
00:56:03,610 --> 00:56:04,709
Thank you, everyone.

1085
00:56:04,745 --> 00:56:06,745
Re pow.

1086
00:56:06,780 --> 00:56:07,712
Magearna!

1087
00:56:18,425 --> 00:56:20,692
[ALL EXCLAIMING]

1088
00:56:41,414 --> 00:56:42,580
Volcanion.

1089
00:56:42,616 --> 00:56:43,548
Weepa.

1090
00:56:50,757 --> 00:56:52,624
If it's soul-heart
is returned,

1091
00:56:52,659 --> 00:56:54,626
Magearna should be revived.

1092
00:56:54,661 --> 00:56:55,593
[GASPING]

1093
00:56:58,765 --> 00:56:59,764
Everyone on board.

1094
00:57:03,403 --> 00:57:06,704
Prince Raleigh, I thought
that you would understand,

1095
00:57:06,740 --> 00:57:08,640
that you would be
able to comprehend

1096
00:57:08,675 --> 00:57:10,675
my noblest of dreams.

1097
00:57:10,710 --> 00:57:13,578
There's no reason to
make such a big fuss.

1098
00:57:13,613 --> 00:57:15,547
We're only talking
about one Pokemon.

1099
00:57:23,723 --> 00:57:27,325
[GASPS] It's Magearna.

1100
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:29,627
I can sense it right from here.

1101
00:57:29,663 --> 00:57:30,595
Oh, Magearna.

1102
00:57:30,630 --> 00:57:32,630
It's crying.

1103
00:57:32,666 --> 00:57:35,600
In that case, it's
retrieved the soul-heart.

1104
00:57:35,635 --> 00:57:37,669
[INAUDIBLE]

1105
00:57:37,704 --> 00:57:39,637
Gengar, psychic.

1106
00:57:39,673 --> 00:57:41,339
Gah!

1107
00:57:41,374 --> 00:57:43,808
You're even less
than useless to me.

1108
00:57:43,844 --> 00:57:45,643
[ALL MOANING]

1109
00:57:45,679 --> 00:57:48,613
[SCREAMING]

1110
00:58:02,362 --> 00:58:04,429
VOLCANION: That
field of flowers,

1111
00:58:04,464 --> 00:58:08,366
that's where I met Magearna
for the very first time.

1112
00:58:08,401 --> 00:58:10,635
Wasn't it 500 years ago?

1113
00:58:10,670 --> 00:58:13,605
I don't know how you
humans measure time.

1114
00:58:13,640 --> 00:58:15,740
But it's a story from
the ancient past.

1115
00:58:30,790 --> 00:58:33,791
Then, as now, the
plateaus. was my home,

1116
00:58:33,827 --> 00:58:37,695
and that of many, many
other troubled Pokemon.

1117
00:58:37,731 --> 00:58:41,699
Oftentimes, I would check the
area for Pokemon that were lost

1118
00:58:41,735 --> 00:58:43,668
and had collapsed
from exhaustion.

1119
00:59:02,389 --> 00:59:04,455
Magearna was the first
one I met that wasn't

1120
